                            <comment id="13879780" author="liushaohui" created="Thu, 23 Jan 2014 08:56:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Confused by the same problem.&lt;br/&gt;
I think we should keep  the &apos;HBASE_OPTS&apos; property user set working.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13879788" author="liushaohui" created="Thu, 23 Jan 2014 09:33:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch for trunk&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13880081" author="nkeywal" created="Thu, 23 Jan 2014 17:04:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ping &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jesse_yates&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jesse_yates&quot;&gt;Jesse Yates&lt;/a&gt; It&apos;s something that we discussed a while ago in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7091&quot; title=&quot;support custom GC options in hbase-env.sh&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-7091&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-7091&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Do you mind having a look?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13880499" author="jesse_yates" created="Thu, 23 Jan 2014 23:16:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok, guess others are using it &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; Looking through hbase-config.sh there are these lines:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
# Source the hbase-env.sh.  Will have JAVA_HOME defined.
# HBASE-7817 - Source the hbase-env.sh only &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; it has not already been done. HBASE_ENV_INIT keeps track of it.
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; [ -z &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;$HBASE_ENV_INIT&quot;&lt;/span&gt; ] &amp;amp;&amp;amp; [ -f &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;${HBASE_CONF_DIR}/hbase-env.sh&quot;&lt;/span&gt; ]; then
  . &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;${HBASE_CONF_DIR}/hbase-env.sh&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
  export HBASE_ENV_INIT=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
fi
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Which should ensure it doesn&apos;t get sourced multiple times - my concern for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7091&quot; title=&quot;support custom GC options in hbase-env.sh&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-7091&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-7091&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Should be fine... you okay with it &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=nkeywal&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;nkeywal&quot;&gt;Nicolas Liochon&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13881024" author="nkeywal" created="Fri, 24 Jan 2014 15:01:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hum. Doesn&apos;t that mean that the first time it will erase the value set in the shell, but not the next time?&lt;br/&gt;
If yes, would it make sense to do something to have something like &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// pseudo code
&lt;/span&gt;HBASE_EXTRA_OPTS=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;-XX:+UseConcMarkSweepGC&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (!HBASE_OPTS.contains(HBASE_EXTRA_OPTS)) HBASE_OPTS  = HBASE_EXTRA_OPTS + HBASE_OPTS
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13881263" author="jesse_yates" created="Fri, 24 Jan 2014 18:29:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It wouldn&apos;t erase it in the shell, I &lt;em&gt;think&lt;/em&gt;, but rather just update it for the the scripts and all child processes. So, the calling shell would still have the variable you set.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As an example, say I have (checked locally on my Mac):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
bash$ export HBASE_OPTS=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;-XX:+UseConcMarkSweepGC&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;and in my hbase-env.sh have&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
HBASE_OPTS=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;$HBASE_OPTS -XX:CustomThingy&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;then after running bin/start-hbase.sh, I would still just see&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
bash$ echo $HBASE_OPTS
-XX:+UseConcMarkSweepGC&quot;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should be fine, yes?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13881442" author="stack" created="Fri, 24 Jan 2014 21:31:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;(Old school showing up late and coming from left field)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When did it become ok picking up config from environment?  I thought that was a no-no from ops 101 (inevitably this &apos;feature&apos; cuts in in surprising ways).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
